Vice President Mike Pence will be visiting Egypt, Jordan, and Israel from January 19-23, 2018 on behalf of President Donald Trump. The purpose of the trip is to address the shared need to combat terrorism and assist persecuted religious minorities. Pence will meet with President Abdel Fattah Al Sisi in Egypt, King Abdullah II in Jordan, and Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and President Reuven Rivlin in Israel. He will also give remarks at the Knesset and visit Yad Vashem and the Western Wall. The trip aims to reaffirm the commitment of the United States to work with its allies in the region to defeat radicalism and improve national security. Additional details about the trip will be announced soon.